NBA ALL-STAR WEEKEND
February 24, 2012
DeMarcus Cousins
START_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT
 
 
  
 
  
  
   
 Q.   After what you did last year do you think you can have a good connection to this year?  
DeMARCUS COUSINS:   Absolutely.   I mean, we're definitely going to have (inaudible.)   Hopefully we can do the same tonight.   
   
 Q.   What are your goals for the second half?  
DeMARCUS COUSINS:   We just want to go on a good run, get on a winning curve.  
   
 Q.   What are you going to do to help the team?  
DeMARCUS COUSINS:   I'm going to do my job every night.   
   
 Q.   Were you always the biggest kid in your class, or did you have a growth spurt somewhere along the line?  
DeMARCUS COUSINS:   I was always tall.   I wasn't always good, though.   
   
 Q.   Did it take some time for your game to catch up to your body?  
DeMARCUS COUSINS:   Actually I started playing ball late.   I haven't been playing long.  
   
 Q.   Was it gradual every year or did you have one summer where you came back‑‑  
DeMARCUS COUSINS:   One summer.  
   
 Q.   When was that?  
DeMARCUS COUSINS:   Ninth grade.   
   
  
  
  
  
  

END_OF_INTERVIEW_TEXT